Faris Al-Khori was jailed for three years and four months after pleading guilty to a breach of the 1883 Explosive Substances Act . 
  Police found bomb-making instructions and recipes for bombs in his Edinburgh flats . 
  The items were discovered by chance during a fire in a rubbish chute . 
  He had dozens of chemicals, poisonous materials and bolts . 
  He also had handwritten notes on how to make a bomb . 
  The 62-year-old pleaded guilty to breaching the explosives act . 
 